1196
01:23:09,343 --> 01:23:11,174
Or incredibly nuts.

1197
01:23:39,663 --> 01:23:41,415
l'm really confused.

1198
01:23:42,743 --> 01:23:43,971
So am l.

1199
01:23:45,103 --> 01:23:48,573
l think l speak for us all
when l thank you for your patience.

1200
01:23:48,823 --> 01:23:52,054
Myself, l have one
final question, Dr. Arroway.

1201
01:23:53,583 --> 01:23:55,778
lf you should meet these Vegans...

1202
01:23:55,983 --> 01:24:00,056
...and were permitted only
one question to ask of them...

1203
01:24:00,223 --> 01:24:01,815
...what would it be?

1204
01:24:03,383 --> 01:24:05,180
l suppose it would be:

1205
01:24:05,343 --> 01:24:06,935
"How did you do it?

1206
01:24:07,503 --> 01:24:11,735
How did you evolve? How did you
survive technological adolescence...

1207
01:24:11,943 --> 01:24:13,854
...without destroying yourself?"

1208
01:24:14,463 --> 01:24:19,173
<i>That more than any other question is</i>
<i>one I personally would like answered.</i>

1209
01:24:19,543 --> 01:24:21,261
Not too bad, Mike.

1210
01:24:21,903 --> 01:24:23,131
<i>I join Dr. Bergeron...</i>

1211
01:24:23,383 --> 01:24:26,580
...in expressing thanks for
your patience, Dr. Arroway.

1212
01:24:26,783 --> 01:24:29,251
We're all impressed
with your candor...

1213
01:24:29,583 --> 01:24:31,062
...and your stamina.

1214
01:24:31,503 --> 01:24:34,700
l think we're ready to move on
to your final statement.

1215
01:24:34,903 --> 01:24:36,655
l have one more question.

1216
01:24:36,903 --> 01:24:38,382
Yes, Mr. Joss.

1217
01:24:42,223 --> 01:24:44,498
Would you consider yourself...

1218
01:24:44,943 --> 01:24:47,173
...a spiritual person?

1219
01:24:52,383 --> 01:24:54,533
l don't understand
the point of the question.

1220
01:24:55,823 --> 01:24:58,462
l consider myself a moral person.

1221
01:24:58,703 --> 01:25:03,094
We're sure that's the case, but what
Mr. Joss is in fact asking...

1222
01:25:03,263 --> 01:25:05,015
Do you believe in God?

1223
01:25:13,183 --> 01:25:15,299
As a scientist...

1224
01:25:15,663 --> 01:25:18,939
...l rely on empirical evidence,
and in this matter...

1225
01:25:19,263 --> 01:25:22,460
...l don't believe
that there's data either way.

1226
01:25:23,263 --> 01:25:27,097
So your answer would in fact be
that you don't believe in God.

1227
01:25:30,783 --> 01:25:33,741
l don't understand the relevance
of the question.

1228
01:25:36,543 --> 01:25:39,455
95%of the world's population...

1229
01:25:39,663 --> 01:25:43,258
...believes in a Supreme Being
in one form or another.

1230
01:25:44,383 --> 01:25:47,500
l believe that makes the question
more than relevant.

1231
01:26:01,303 --> 01:26:02,782
l believe...

1232
01:26:06,943 --> 01:26:09,411
l believe l've already
answered that question.

1233
01:26:13,263 --> 01:26:16,539
<i>I'm proud of what</i>
<i>we've achieved as a species...</i>

1234
01:26:16,823 --> 01:26:18,734
<i>...and as a civilization.</i>

1235
01:26:20,303 --> 01:26:22,817
<i>I would hate to see</i>
<i>everything we stand for...</i>

1236
01:26:23,023 --> 01:26:26,572
<i>...all that we have fought for</i>
<i>for a thousand generations...</i>

1237
01:26:26,783 --> 01:26:29,092
<i>...all that God</i>
<i>has blessed us with...</i>

1238
01:26:30,383 --> 01:26:31,816
...betrayed...

1239
01:26:32,703 --> 01:26:37,174
...in the final hour because we sent a
representative who did not put our...

1240
01:26:37,663 --> 01:26:40,302
<i>...most cherished beliefs first.</i>

1241
01:26:43,423 --> 01:26:44,572
<i>Thank you.</i>

1242
01:27:16,463 --> 01:27:17,737
Why'd you do it?

1243
01:27:22,143 --> 01:27:26,102
Our job was to select someone
to speak for everybody.

1244
01:27:29,343 --> 01:27:32,494
l couldn't in good conscience
vote for a person...

1245
01:27:32,703 --> 01:27:34,659
...who doesn't believe in God.

1246
01:27:36,623 --> 01:27:37,942
Someone who...

1247
01:27:38,423 --> 01:27:41,381
...honestly thinks
the other 95%of us...

1248
01:27:41,583 --> 01:27:44,222
...suffer from some form
of mass delusion.

1249
01:27:47,503 --> 01:27:49,459
l told the truth up there.

1250
01:27:50,743 --> 01:27:54,053
Drumlin told you exactly
what you wanted to hear.

1251
01:28:27,743 --> 01:28:30,257
<i>With full humility</i>
<i>and utmost gratitude...</i>

1252
01:28:30,463 --> 01:28:32,499
<i>...I accept this great honor...</i>

1253
01:28:32,703 --> 01:28:36,616
<i>...and I promise I will do my best</i>
<i>to represent my nation...</i>

1254
01:28:36,823 --> 01:28:40,133
<i>...my planet and my God</i>
<i>on this historic...</i>

1255
01:28:40,303 --> 01:28:41,338
<i>...journey.</i>

1256
01:28:41,823 --> 01:28:44,053
<i>I thank you</i>
<i>from the bottom of my heart.</i>

1257
01:29:24,983 --> 01:29:27,816
<i>There's a carnival atmosphere</i>
<i>at Cape Canaveral...</i>

1258
01:29:27,983 --> 01:29:30,019
<i>...as the International</i>
<i>Machine Consortium...</i>

1259
01:29:30,223 --> 01:29:33,420
<i>...hosts as much a media event</i>
<i>as a systems test.</i>

1260
01:29:33,823 --> 01:29:37,418
<i>David Drumlin is supervising</i>
<i>the on</i>-<i>site portion of the test.</i>

1261
01:29:37,583 --> 01:29:39,380
<i>We spoke with him earlier today.</i>

1262
01:29:39,583 --> 01:29:41,255
<i>We'll be able to monitor</i>
<i>the stresses and effects...</i>

1263
01:29:41,463 --> 01:29:44,261
<i>...using the robot passenger...</i>

1264
01:29:44,703 --> 01:29:46,978
<i>... who we lovingly call Elmer.</i>

1265
01:29:52,503 --> 01:29:54,858
The press wants to
ask you a few questions...

1266
01:29:55,063 --> 01:29:57,623
...as soon as they're done
with Dr. Drumlin.

1267
01:30:00,103 --> 01:30:01,855
When we release the pod...

1268
01:30:02,223 --> 01:30:04,578
...a substantial amount of energy
will be generated.

1269
01:30:05,303 --> 01:30:07,863
We'll be able to monitor
the stresses and effects...

1270
01:30:08,063 --> 01:30:10,338
...using our robot passenger,
who we...

1271
01:30:10,583 --> 01:30:12,574
...lovingly call Elmer.

1272
01:30:13,143 --> 01:30:14,132
Thank you.

1273
01:30:14,343 --> 01:30:15,537
You're welcome.

1274
01:30:16,943 --> 01:30:19,093
They're ready for you
out at the site.

1275
01:30:19,743 --> 01:30:21,301
Yeah, just a minute.

1276
01:30:27,183 --> 01:30:29,378
-Congratulations.
-Glad you could come.

1277
01:30:30,623 --> 01:30:32,978
Didn't expect to see you here.

1278
01:30:33,703 --> 01:30:35,455
Well, l'm still...

1279
01:30:35,823 --> 01:30:38,337
...Crew Ops at the Control Center.

1280
01:30:38,983 --> 01:30:42,896
l suppose the fact that l discovered
the message means l have PR value.

1281
01:30:43,103 --> 01:30:44,456
Of course.

1282
01:30:46,103 --> 01:30:49,140
l know you must think
this is all very unfair.

1283
01:30:49,703 --> 01:30:51,614
And maybe that's an understatement.

1284
01:30:52,983 --> 01:30:55,213
What you don't know is, l agree.

1285
01:30:55,783 --> 01:30:58,900
l wish the world was a place
where fair was the bottom line...

1286
01:30:59,063 --> 01:31:02,260
...where the idealism you showed
at the hearing was rewarded...

1287
01:31:02,463 --> 01:31:04,499
...not taken advantage of.

1288
01:31:06,183 --> 01:31:08,902
Unfortunately,
we don't live in that world.

1289
01:31:11,143 --> 01:31:12,178
Funny...

1290
01:31:13,583 --> 01:31:16,575
...l always believed the world
is what we make of it.

1291
01:31:18,503 --> 01:31:19,299
Excuse me!

1292
01:31:23,063 --> 01:31:24,576
Good luck on the test.

1293
01:31:25,263 --> 01:31:26,378
Thank you.

1294
01:31:34,583 --> 01:31:35,572
<i>Test director...</i>

1295
01:31:35,783 --> 01:31:37,933
<i>...everything looks good.</i>
<i>Ready to go.</i>

1296
01:31:38,423 --> 01:31:41,335
l want things double
and triple-checked here.

1297
01:31:41,543 --> 01:31:44,615
We only get one shot at this.
Let's get it right.

1298
01:31:45,143 --> 01:31:48,021
Ladies and gentlemen,
we are ready for start-up.

1299
01:31:48,223 --> 01:31:51,420
All controllers, l need a go-no-go
for test initiation.

1300
01:31:51,663 --> 01:31:52,539
-Mechanical?
-Go.

1301
01:31:52,783 --> 01:31:53,693
Electrical?

1302
01:31:53,863 --> 01:31:54,852
Dynamics?

1303
01:31:55,063 --> 01:31:56,212
Communications?

1304
01:31:56,463 --> 01:31:57,532
Pod systems?

1305
01:31:57,703 --> 01:31:58,818
Safety?

1306
01:31:59,263 --> 01:32:01,982
Crew Ops, verify all pre-test
procedures are complete.

1307
01:32:02,263 --> 01:32:03,582
Yes, verified.
l'm go.

1308
01:32:03,783 --> 01:32:06,172
Pad Leader,
is everything okay with you?

1309
01:32:06,343 --> 01:32:08,811
<i>Roger. The pad is a go.</i>

1310
01:32:09,103 --> 01:32:11,697
Test initiation, on my mark.

1311
01:32:12,183 --> 01:32:13,377
5...

1312
01:32:13,743 --> 01:32:14,858
...4...

1313
01:32:15,223 --> 01:32:16,338
...3...

1314
01:32:16,623 --> 01:32:17,578
...2...

1315
01:32:18,103 --> 01:32:19,138
...1 .

1316
01:32:19,663 --> 01:32:20,732
Mark.

1317
01:32:21,223 --> 01:32:22,941
-Test start.
-Rings are unlocked.

1318
01:32:23,143 --> 01:32:24,656
Power levels show a good start.

1319
01:32:24,823 --> 01:32:26,575
<i>We've begun the test of...</i>

1320
01:32:26,743 --> 01:32:31,134
<i>...earth's first system built by sharing</i>
<i>knowledge with a neighbor in space.</i>

1321
01:32:31,303 --> 01:32:33,453
All power sources
on core induction bus.

1322
01:32:33,623 --> 01:32:35,295
lPV power transfer.

1323
01:32:35,503 --> 01:32:38,540
Ring motion detect.
Alpha, Bravo, Charlie.

1324
01:32:40,023 --> 01:32:42,981
-Gerry, how are we looking?
-Looks good. We're underway.

1325
01:32:43,143 --> 01:32:44,861
Looks like a normal start-up.

1326
01:32:45,063 --> 01:32:47,338
Roger, David.
lt's looking good here.

1327
01:32:52,663 --> 01:32:55,894
<i>We are moments away from</i>
<i>the initiation of the drop sequence.</i>

1328
01:32:56,143 --> 01:32:57,781
<i>All systems are go.</i>

1329
01:33:00,663 --> 01:33:02,415
-Mechanical, you still happy?
-Roger.

1330
01:33:02,583 --> 01:33:03,857
<i>It's very exciting...</i>

1331
01:33:04,023 --> 01:33:05,581
<i>...from up here.</i>

1332
01:33:07,823 --> 01:33:09,495
We've got 4%.

1333
01:33:09,663 --> 01:33:11,415
<i>We're confirming 4%.</i>

1334
01:33:12,583 --> 01:33:15,177
<i>Frequency 9.85.</i>

1335
01:33:16,143 --> 01:33:18,054
<i>Harmonics in the green.</i>

1336
01:33:18,263 --> 01:33:20,458
<i>G</i>-<i>level 1. 1.</i>

1337
01:33:21,583 --> 01:33:24,814
-5%.
-Confirmed. We are at 5%.

1338
01:33:24,983 --> 01:33:26,541
David, how's it looking to you?

1339
01:33:26,823 --> 01:33:29,656
<i>Okay. I'm going to take a look</i>
<i>and show you what we got.</i>

1340
01:33:29,823 --> 01:33:31,575
<i>Instrumentation looks good.</i>

1341
01:33:31,743 --> 01:33:35,099
We have a good picture
from Dr. Drumlin's PRD.

1342
01:33:35,623 --> 01:33:37,932
<i>Hope you guys are seeing</i>
<i>what I'm seeing.</i>

1343
01:33:38,463 --> 01:33:40,215
<i>All systems are go.</i>

1344
01:33:41,703 --> 01:33:43,216
<i>This is really something!</i>

1345
01:33:43,383 --> 01:33:44,941
<i>For purposes of this test...</i>

1346
01:33:45,143 --> 01:33:49,261
<i>...Dr. Drumlin will be on top of the</i>
<i>Gantry crane that's over the Machine.</i>

1347
01:33:49,463 --> 01:33:51,419
<i>We've got some video animation...</i>

1348
01:33:51,663 --> 01:33:54,939
<i>...to show just how this Machine...</i>
<i>it is thought... will work.</i>

1349
01:33:55,143 --> 01:33:56,735
<i>The passenger pod will release.</i>

1350
01:33:56,943 --> 01:33:59,173
<i>It will come down</i>
<i>through the center of the rings...</i>

1351
01:33:59,383 --> 01:34:01,135
<i>...and into the Machine's core.</i>

1352
01:34:01,343 --> 01:34:03,538
<i>The question everyone</i>
<i>here is asking is...</i>

1353
01:34:03,783 --> 01:34:05,216
<i>... what happens then?</i>

1354
01:34:05,423 --> 01:34:06,981
<i>Some believe the rings function...</i>

1355
01:34:07,183 --> 01:34:10,016
<i>...as some sort of an accelerator</i>
<i>or something...</i>

1356
01:34:10,743 --> 01:34:12,813
<i>...sending its energy</i>
<i>into the pod...</i>

1357
01:34:12,983 --> 01:34:15,372
<i>...making it rocket away</i>
<i>at near light speed.</i>

1358
01:34:15,583 --> 01:34:19,895
<i>Others believe it might open up</i>
<i>a doorway to some other dimension.</i>

1359
01:34:20,183 --> 01:34:21,138
<i>Who's right?</i>

1360
01:34:21,423 --> 01:34:23,698
<i>That's what</i>
<i>today's test is all about.</i>

1361
01:34:24,143 --> 01:34:26,213
-35%.
-Subsystems ready?

1362
01:34:26,423 --> 01:34:28,254
40%normal acceleration.

1363
01:34:28,423 --> 01:34:29,697
<i>Confirm 40%.</i>

1364
01:34:29,903 --> 01:34:32,736
Controllers stand by
to initiate drop sequence...

1365
01:34:32,983 --> 01:34:34,416
...on my mark.

1366
01:34:34,623 --> 01:34:36,693
<i>All systems ready for drop sequence.</i>

1367
01:34:36,983 --> 01:34:38,462
45%.

1368
01:34:39,343 --> 01:34:41,413
<i>We're in 45%.</i>

1369
01:34:42,303 --> 01:34:44,294
<i>Verify closure.</i>

1370
01:34:45,543 --> 01:34:46,771
46.

1371
01:34:47,183 --> 01:34:51,654
All controllers stand by to initiate
lPV drop sequence. On my mark.

1372
01:34:52,303 --> 01:34:53,622
48%.

1373
01:34:54,823 --> 01:34:56,893
<i>I'm feeling</i>
<i>a very strange vibration.</i>

1374
01:34:57,343 --> 01:35:00,255
-<i>Are you feeling it down there?</i>
-Gerry, can you confirm?

1375
01:35:00,823 --> 01:35:02,017
Everything looks good.

1376
01:35:02,743 --> 01:35:03,619
Crew Ops?

1377
01:35:03,863 --> 01:35:04,739
Nothing wrong.

1378
01:35:04,903 --> 01:35:06,461
We see nothing abnormal here.

1379
01:35:06,663 --> 01:35:09,382
<i>No good. Hold sequence.</i>
<i>I'll take a direct reading.</i>

1380
01:35:09,823 --> 01:35:11,176
What's he talking about?

1381
01:35:11,423 --> 01:35:12,981
Can anyone say grandstanding?

1382
01:35:13,303 --> 01:35:15,214
He sure knows he's on TV!

1383
01:35:15,423 --> 01:35:18,256
Back home that's what we call
an overcooked ham.

1384
01:35:18,623 --> 01:35:20,693
<i>I'm reading 10 kilohertz!</i>

1385
01:35:21,063 --> 01:35:23,736
<i>What do you read on the first</i>
<i>and second order G</i>-<i>levels?</i>

1386
01:35:23,943 --> 01:35:25,501
G-levels are right on!

1387
01:35:27,263 --> 01:35:30,061
<i>We confirm Drumlin's readings.</i>
<i>All normal. We're go.</i>

1388
01:35:31,263 --> 01:35:33,823
l think we're okay,
but we'll let him finish.

1389
01:35:35,103 --> 01:35:38,334
-Mechanical, you still okay?
-Roger. Right on the money.

1390
01:35:38,743 --> 01:35:39,892
Security problem!

1391
01:35:41,223 --> 01:35:42,781
Ellie, are you sure?

1392
01:35:43,423 --> 01:35:44,981
He shouldn't be there.
l know him.

1393
01:35:45,183 --> 01:35:47,856
Gerry, execute the
rapid shutdown sequence.

1394
01:35:48,103 --> 01:35:51,140
Security, move emergency
response team into position.

1395
01:35:51,383 --> 01:35:53,135
Get Drumlin on a secure loop.

1396
01:35:53,383 --> 01:35:54,702
You got him.

1397
01:35:54,943 --> 01:35:57,298
-Can you hear me?
-<i>Yes, I hear.</i>

1398
01:35:57,703 --> 01:35:59,739
We've got a security breach here.

1399
01:36:00,103 --> 01:36:01,058
Behind you.

1400
01:36:01,303 --> 01:36:02,133
The tall guy.

1401
01:36:02,543 --> 01:36:03,817
The technician.

1402
01:36:04,183 --> 01:36:05,218
See him?

1403
01:36:07,583 --> 01:36:08,777
He shouldn't be there.

1404
01:36:14,623 --> 01:36:16,022
Something's in his hand!

1405
01:36:17,103 --> 01:36:19,856
<i>Him! Take him!</i>
<i>Security breach!</i>

1406
01:36:20,143 --> 01:36:20,939
A bomb!

1407
01:36:21,223 --> 01:36:24,454
l want that emergency response team
up on the gantry. Now!

1408
01:36:24,783 --> 01:36:25,693
Stage One Alert!

1409
01:36:25,903 --> 01:36:28,542
Move all fire and rescue personnel
into position one.

1410
01:37:05,263 --> 01:37:07,299
All right, back to your stations.

1411
01:37:07,543 --> 01:37:10,501
l need you to be professional.
Settle down!

1412
01:37:10,663 --> 01:37:13,018
Pad Leader, do you copy?

1413
01:37:30,223 --> 01:37:32,691
<i>The scene earlier today,</i>
<i>when David Drumlin...</i>

1414
01:37:32,863 --> 01:37:34,694
<i>...advisor to two Presidents...</i>

1415
01:37:34,863 --> 01:37:38,572
<i>...and winner of the National Academy</i>
<i>of Sciences lifetime award...</i>

1416
01:37:38,863 --> 01:37:42,378
<i>... was laid to rest</i>
<i>at Arlington National Cemetery.</i>

1417
01:37:46,063 --> 01:37:47,735
<i>In a related story...</i>

1418
01:37:47,943 --> 01:37:49,171
Can l help you?

1419
01:37:51,103 --> 01:37:52,980
l've got some mail for you.

1420
01:37:53,343 --> 01:37:57,734
<i>...the apparent suicide note of the</i>
<i>terrorist now believed responsible...</i>

1421
01:37:57,903 --> 01:38:00,701
<i>...for the explosion</i>
<i>in Florida this week.</i>

1422
01:38:01,023 --> 01:38:02,581
<i>What we do...</i>

1423
01:38:02,863 --> 01:38:05,661
<i>... we do for the goodness</i>
<i>of all mankind.</i>

1424
01:38:06,423 --> 01:38:09,142
<i>This won't be understood,</i>
<i>not now...</i>

1425
01:38:09,503 --> 01:38:11,175
<i>...but the Apocalypse to come...</i>

1426
01:38:12,223 --> 01:38:14,293
<i>... will vindicate our faith.</i>

1427
01:38:37,663 --> 01:38:38,459
Welcome home.

1428
01:39:42,463 --> 01:39:43,942
<i>Comrade Arroway...</i>

1429
01:39:44,903 --> 01:39:48,134
<i>... we have been expecting your call.</i>
<i>One moment, please.</i>

1430
01:39:57,503 --> 01:39:58,652
Mr. Hadden?

1431
01:39:59,223 --> 01:40:00,542
<i>Doctor!</i>

1432
01:40:01,583 --> 01:40:03,335
<i>How kind of you to call.</i>

1433
01:40:03,943 --> 01:40:05,854
Mr. Hadden, where are you?

1434
01:40:07,983 --> 01:40:08,972
<i>The Russian government...</i>

1435
01:40:09,143 --> 01:40:12,374
<i>... was kind enough</i>
<i>to give me accommodations on Mir.</i>

1436
01:40:13,343 --> 01:40:15,095
You're living on a space station?

1437
01:40:16,423 --> 01:40:18,334
<i>It's quite simple, really.</i>

1438
01:40:19,743 --> 01:40:23,053
<i>The low oxygen,</i>
<i>zero gravity environment...</i>

1439
01:40:23,263 --> 01:40:27,734
<i>...is the only thing keeping</i>
<i>the cancer from eating me alive.</i>

1440
01:40:29,343 --> 01:40:31,857
<i>Actually, I quite like it up here.</i>

1441
01:40:32,383 --> 01:40:35,420
<i>My little room</i>
<i>has one hell of a view.</i>

1442
01:40:43,223 --> 01:40:44,975
<i>I want to show you something.</i>

1443
01:40:49,503 --> 01:40:51,414
<i>Hokkaido Island.</i>

1444
01:40:52,663 --> 01:40:54,779
The systems integration site.

1445
01:40:55,863 --> 01:40:57,342
<i>Look closer.</i>

1446
01:41:05,343 --> 01:41:08,062
<i>First rule in government spending:</i>

1447
01:41:09,023 --> 01:41:12,698
<i>Why build one when you can have</i>
<i>two at twice the price?</i>

1448
01:41:13,023 --> 01:41:15,901
<i>Only, this one can be kept secret.</i>

1449
01:41:16,543 --> 01:41:18,499
<i>Controlled by Americans...</i>

1450
01:41:18,903 --> 01:41:22,134
<i>...built by Japanese</i>
<i>subcontractors...</i>

1451
01:41:23,023 --> 01:41:25,537
<i>... who also happen to be...</i>

1452
01:41:26,463 --> 01:41:28,055
<i>...recently acquired...</i>

1453
01:41:28,583 --> 01:41:30,972
<i>... wholly</i>-<i>owned subsidiaries...</i>

1454
01:41:31,783 --> 01:41:33,694
...of Hadden lndustries.

1455
01:41:37,183 --> 01:41:40,255
<i>They still want</i>
<i>an American to go, Doctor.</i>

1456
01:41:43,863 --> 01:41:45,342
<i>Want to take a ride?</i>

1457
01:42:26,303 --> 01:42:28,214
<i>Augmenting our restraint and...</i>

1458
01:42:28,423 --> 01:42:30,459
...communications console
subsystem...

1459
01:42:30,623 --> 01:42:32,534
...is your personal recording unit.

1460
01:42:32,823 --> 01:42:36,213
Normal,
infrared and ultraviolet lenses.

1461
01:42:36,863 --> 01:42:40,572
Digital microchip good for
thousands of hours of recording.

1462
01:42:41,863 --> 01:42:43,933
Okay, look, l understand...

1463
01:42:44,183 --> 01:42:47,414
...the reason for recording
and documenting the mission.

1464
01:42:47,623 --> 01:42:50,012
But l just want to go on record
one more time.

1465
01:42:50,303 --> 01:42:53,613
The transmitted specs never said
anything about any chair...

1466
01:42:53,823 --> 01:42:55,654
...or a restraining harness...

1467
01:42:55,863 --> 01:42:57,774
...or survival gear.

1468
01:42:58,463 --> 01:43:00,215
Why can't we just trust
the original...

1469
01:43:00,383 --> 01:43:04,217
Doctor, both the lMC Board and
the Sl team reviewed the matter...

1470
01:43:04,383 --> 01:43:07,819
...and concluded that the design
impact is negligible.

1471
01:43:08,183 --> 01:43:09,662
Bottom line is...

1472
01:43:10,143 --> 01:43:12,213
...we're not putting anyone
aboard this Machine...

1473
01:43:12,423 --> 01:43:15,301
...unless there is
some sort of minimal protection.

1474
01:43:15,583 --> 01:43:16,857
End of story.

1475
01:43:23,583 --> 01:43:27,417
We've given these to the astronauts
since the start of the space program.

1476
01:43:28,743 --> 01:43:30,938
lt's never been made public,
of course.

1477
01:43:31,103 --> 01:43:33,139
lt's fast and it's painless.

1478
01:43:35,743 --> 01:43:38,621
l'm going to travel 26 light years
to commit suicide?

1479
01:43:38,903 --> 01:43:40,541
Something may go wrong.

1480
01:43:41,023 --> 01:43:43,583
There may be
an unforeseen mechanical failure.

1481
01:43:44,383 --> 01:43:47,261
You could be marooned,
unable to return.

1482
01:43:48,383 --> 01:43:51,420
There are 1,000 reasons
we can think of to have this...

1483
01:43:51,583 --> 01:43:54,416
...but mostly it's for the reasons
we can't think of.

1484
01:44:19,903 --> 01:44:20,972
Come in.

1485
01:44:22,463 --> 01:44:24,693
Dr. Arroway, time to get ready.

1486
01:44:24,863 --> 01:44:25,818
Thank you.

1487
01:44:36,503 --> 01:44:38,141
l know there's not much time.

1488
01:44:38,303 --> 01:44:41,261
As soon as l found out about it,
l called the President.

1489
01:44:41,463 --> 01:44:43,055
l came with Kitz.

1490
01:44:43,623 --> 01:44:45,818
l had to see you one more time.

1491
01:44:45,983 --> 01:44:47,621
Oh, God, l'm sorry.

1492
01:44:48,023 --> 01:44:49,661
No, l'm glad you came.

1493
01:44:49,943 --> 01:44:52,059
There's something
l got to say to you.

1494
01:44:53,383 --> 01:44:57,456
The reason l didn't vote for you was
a good one, but not the real one.

1495
01:44:58,463 --> 01:45:00,374
l didn't vote for you to go...

1496
01:45:02,183 --> 01:45:03,980
...because l don't want to lose you.

1497
01:45:05,023 --> 01:45:07,093
Now you find your way home,
all right?

1498
01:45:23,423 --> 01:45:24,822
<i>23 hours ago, the world...</i>

1499
01:45:25,023 --> 01:45:28,982
<i>... was stunned by the announcement</i>
<i>of the existence of another Machine...</i>

1500
01:45:29,143 --> 01:45:31,976
<i>...and its passenger,</i>
<i>Eleanor Ann Arroway.</i>

1501
01:45:32,183 --> 01:45:32,740
<i>Now...</i>

1502
01:45:33,343 --> 01:45:35,698
<i>...the question</i>
<i>that's on everyone's mind:</i>

1503
01:45:35,863 --> 01:45:37,535
<i>Will history repeat itself?</i>

1504
01:45:37,943 --> 01:45:40,173
<i>With a piece of engineering</i>
<i>this complex...</i>

1505
01:45:40,383 --> 01:45:44,217
<i>... with so many unknowns,</i>
<i>could the unthinkable occur?</i>

1506
01:45:44,383 --> 01:45:47,580
<i>The security in Hokkaido</i>
<i>has been incredibly tight.</i>

1507
01:45:47,743 --> 01:45:51,019
<i>No reporters whatsoever</i>
<i>have been allowed near the site.</i>

1508
01:48:24,943 --> 01:48:27,821
Restraint secure.
Life support functions normal.

1509
01:48:28,023 --> 01:48:28,853
Roger.

1510
01:48:29,023 --> 01:48:30,979
<i>This is Control.</i>
<i>Do you copy?</i>

1511
01:48:31,263 --> 01:48:32,582
Reading you five-by-five.

1512
01:48:33,623 --> 01:48:35,056
Give me Ellie's PRD.

1513
01:48:35,263 --> 01:48:37,174
<i>Video unit recording</i>
<i>and transmitting.</i>

1514
01:48:38,463 --> 01:48:40,977
-<i>Are you reading me?</i>
-That's affirmative.

1515
01:48:41,143 --> 01:48:42,781
Video looks good.

1516
01:48:43,583 --> 01:48:44,652
<i>Copy, Control.</i>

1517
01:48:45,983 --> 01:48:48,702
Ellie, we're going to proceed
to button you up.

1518
01:48:50,503 --> 01:48:51,572
<i>I'm ready.</i>

1519
01:48:55,303 --> 01:48:57,055
<i>Confirming walkway retraction.</i>

1520
01:48:57,743 --> 01:48:59,096
-Communications?
-Go.

1521
01:48:59,263 --> 01:49:01,174
-Life support?
-Go.

1522
01:49:01,503 --> 01:49:02,856
We are go for closure.

1523
01:49:05,183 --> 01:49:06,821
<i>I'm go here.</i>

1524
01:49:07,823 --> 01:49:11,133
Mechanical, initiate
lPV closure sequence.

1525
01:49:12,703 --> 01:49:14,375
Let me get you a chair.

1526
01:49:16,703 --> 01:49:19,900
-lt's nice to smell you again, Mr. Kitz.
-You too.

1527
01:49:20,583 --> 01:49:22,335
Wouldn't peg him as a Polo man.

1528
01:49:31,343 --> 01:49:32,776
l got a visual on the door.

1529
01:49:35,103 --> 01:49:36,855
The door is looking good.

1530
01:49:41,903 --> 01:49:43,495
Door alignment looks good.

1531
01:50:11,543 --> 01:50:12,976
We're green across the board.

1532
01:50:13,183 --> 01:50:15,572
Copy that, Control.
lPV is secure.

1533
01:50:23,103 --> 01:50:24,695
<i>We are at 30%.</i>

1534
01:50:25,183 --> 01:50:26,502
Copy that, 30%.

1535
01:50:31,143 --> 01:50:32,542
How you doing in there?

1536
01:50:33,063 --> 01:50:33,654
<i>Kent?</i>

1537
01:50:34,543 --> 01:50:35,259
ls that you?

1538
01:50:35,663 --> 01:50:37,176
<i>That's a big affirmative.</i>

1539
01:50:38,023 --> 01:50:39,456
Who let you in there?

1540
01:50:39,783 --> 01:50:41,694
<i>A higher power intervened.</i>

1541
01:50:43,663 --> 01:50:45,016
l'm glad you came.

1542
01:50:49,503 --> 01:50:50,618
35%.

1543
01:50:51,383 --> 01:50:52,657
Copy that, 35%.

1544
01:50:52,903 --> 01:50:54,302
-Mechanical?
-We're good.

1545
01:50:54,463 --> 01:50:55,782
40%.

1546
01:50:59,143 --> 01:51:01,054
l'm picking up a moderate vibration.

1547
01:51:02,183 --> 01:51:04,139
Dynamics, can you confirm vibration?

1548
01:51:04,343 --> 01:51:05,492
lt looks good here.

1549
01:51:05,743 --> 01:51:08,815
She's feeling the same thing
they felt at the Cape.

1550
01:51:08,983 --> 01:51:10,018
Vibration's normal.

1551
01:51:10,743 --> 01:51:13,018
<i>We are at 50%.</i>
<i>All systems nominal.</i>

1552
01:51:13,303 --> 01:51:15,021
Copy that, 50%.

1553
01:51:20,263 --> 01:51:22,094
Vibration's a little stronger now.

1554
01:51:22,383 --> 01:51:24,578
We're picking up
some low frequency noise.

1555
01:51:25,383 --> 01:51:26,862
Mechanical, confirm?

1556
01:51:27,063 --> 01:51:28,382
lt looks fine to me.

1557
01:51:28,583 --> 01:51:30,653
Roger.
Jerry, what do you think?

1558
01:51:30,863 --> 01:51:31,693
l'm still go.

1559
01:51:31,903 --> 01:51:33,382
People, we are still go.

1560
01:51:36,063 --> 01:51:37,542
Something's happening.

1561
01:51:41,463 --> 01:51:42,816
You see that light?

1562
01:51:43,063 --> 01:51:44,132
<i>I'm seeing</i>...

1563
01:51:47,263 --> 01:51:49,140
l can't tell if it's daylight.

1564
01:51:49,903 --> 01:51:52,292
There it is again.
lt's coming from the bottom.

1565
01:51:53,703 --> 01:51:55,216
Let me show you.
See that?

1566
01:51:55,423 --> 01:51:57,539
Negative.
You're breaking up.

1567
01:51:57,863 --> 01:51:59,933
-Can we boost signal?
-lt's at maximum.

1568
01:52:00,423 --> 01:52:01,651
65%.

1569
01:52:01,823 --> 01:52:03,461
<i>The material is changing.</i>

1570
01:52:03,623 --> 01:52:06,979
lt's bordering on translucence.
The system's intact.

1571
01:52:10,183 --> 01:52:11,662
lt has to be...

1572
01:52:11,903 --> 01:52:14,258
...some kind of
electromagnetic field.

1573
01:52:14,503 --> 01:52:15,538
<i>Do you read this?</i>

1574
01:52:15,783 --> 01:52:17,296
We see only interference.

1575
01:52:17,463 --> 01:52:19,181
<i>It's becoming translucent.</i>

1576
01:52:20,023 --> 01:52:22,457
l can't describe it.
l can't even explain it!

1577
01:52:25,063 --> 01:52:25,973
70%.

1578
01:52:26,183 --> 01:52:28,458
We have intermittent comm,
but we are go!

1579
01:52:28,783 --> 01:52:30,694
lnitiate secondary drive systems.

1580
01:52:30,903 --> 01:52:32,859
lnitiating
auxiliary booster sequence.

1581
01:52:33,103 --> 01:52:34,582
We're go for ignition.

1582
01:52:41,663 --> 01:52:43,096
We have auxiliary ignition.

1583
01:52:49,423 --> 01:52:50,822
Life support, how is she?

1584
01:52:51,023 --> 01:52:53,742
Heart and respiration are high
but within limits.

1585
01:52:54,103 --> 01:52:55,377
Ellie, do you copy?

1586
01:52:55,543 --> 01:52:56,419
<i>If you hear...</i>

1587
01:52:56,623 --> 01:52:58,420
...l am okay to go.

1588
01:53:06,783 --> 01:53:07,932
80%.

1589
01:53:08,223 --> 01:53:10,942
All vibration and G-levels
are in the green.

1590
01:53:16,103 --> 01:53:18,298
Control, if you're reading me...

1591
01:53:18,503 --> 01:53:20,653
...l am okay to go!
Okay to go!

1592
01:53:20,903 --> 01:53:21,813
85%.

1593
01:53:22,063 --> 01:53:23,416
All tips are on the profile.

1594
01:53:25,503 --> 01:53:28,381
90%. We're detecting
some structural instability.

1595
01:53:29,503 --> 01:53:32,301
-ls she holding?
-We're within limits, barely.

1596
01:53:33,743 --> 01:53:35,654
l'm okay to go!

1597
01:53:37,543 --> 01:53:39,101
l'm okay to go!

1598
01:53:45,143 --> 01:53:46,496
My God!

1599
01:53:57,103 --> 01:53:58,456
Okay to go!

1600
01:53:58,663 --> 01:53:59,652
l'm okay!

1601
01:53:59,903 --> 01:54:01,336
100%target velocity.

1602
01:54:02,783 --> 01:54:06,935
Tremendous EMl levels around Machine!
Field measurements are off-scale.

1603
01:54:07,183 --> 01:54:09,378
We're approaching our abort limits.

1604
01:54:11,783 --> 01:54:12,932
Okay to go.

1605
01:54:17,863 --> 01:54:18,659
l hear her!

1606
01:54:19,183 --> 01:54:21,981
l hear her.
Barely, but she's there.

1607
01:54:22,223 --> 01:54:23,372
Okay to go.

1608
01:54:23,663 --> 01:54:25,016
Says she's okay to go.

1609
01:54:27,903 --> 01:54:29,655
Steve, we're real close.

1610
01:54:29,983 --> 01:54:32,861
-Your core reading?
-lnternal environment looks normal.

1611
01:54:33,263 --> 01:54:35,857
lnside the core,
the weather's beautiful.

1612
01:54:39,783 --> 01:54:41,011
l'm okay to go.

1613
01:54:43,383 --> 01:54:44,862
l'm okay to go.

1614
01:54:45,303 --> 01:54:46,656
<i>Initiate drop sequence.</i>

1615
01:54:49,983 --> 01:54:51,701
On my mark.

1616
01:54:52,383 --> 01:54:53,338
10...

1617
01:54:53,783 --> 01:54:54,772
...9...

1618
01:54:55,743 --> 01:54:56,698
<i>...8...</i>

1619
01:54:58,183 --> 01:54:59,138
<i>... 7...</i>

1620
01:54:59,543 --> 01:55:00,498
<i>...6...</i>

1621
01:55:01,063 --> 01:55:02,018
...5...

1622
01:55:02,303 --> 01:55:03,258
...4...

1623
01:55:03,783 --> 01:55:04,374
...3...

1624
01:55:05,303 --> 01:55:06,213
<i>...2...</i>

1625
01:55:06,423 --> 01:55:07,412
l'm okay to go.

1626
01:55:11,583 --> 01:55:13,141
Oh, God!

1627
01:55:22,303 --> 01:55:23,895
Ellie to Control.

1628
01:55:24,543 --> 01:55:26,977
Ellie to Control,
do you read me!

1629
01:55:31,423 --> 01:55:33,698
Ellie to Control,
do you read me!

1630
01:55:39,583 --> 01:55:40,698
l'll try...

1631
01:55:41,503 --> 01:55:42,902
...to keep recording!

1632
01:55:43,583 --> 01:55:45,175
l'm going through...

1633
01:55:45,343 --> 01:55:47,254
...some kind of a tunnel!

1634
01:56:02,103 --> 01:56:03,582
There's a light source ahead!

1635
01:56:04,223 --> 01:56:05,292
Brilliant...

1636
01:56:05,503 --> 01:56:06,731
...blue-white.

1637
01:56:08,383 --> 01:56:09,816
Residual radiation?

1638
01:56:21,063 --> 01:56:22,337
lt's a star.

1639
01:56:22,903 --> 01:56:24,018
l must have...

1640
01:56:24,703 --> 01:56:26,136
...gone through a wormhole.

1641
01:56:31,143 --> 01:56:32,371
lt's Vega!

1642
01:56:43,103 --> 01:56:44,855
l'm in another wormhole now!

1643
01:56:48,383 --> 01:56:49,452
<i>I had no idea!</i>

1644
01:56:49,663 --> 01:56:51,096
A series of them!

1645
01:56:53,983 --> 01:56:55,132
<i>They're alive.</i>

1646
01:56:55,343 --> 01:56:56,412
lt's like...

1647
01:56:56,823 --> 01:56:59,132
...some kind of a transit system.

1648
01:57:00,103 --> 01:57:01,422
A subway!

1649
01:57:01,623 --> 01:57:02,942
<i>Oh, God!</i>

1650
01:57:08,383 --> 01:57:10,260
l have to keep talking.

1651
01:57:13,183 --> 01:57:14,457
lt's a triple...

1652
01:57:14,623 --> 01:57:16,818
...no, a quadruple system.

1653
01:57:17,383 --> 01:57:18,418
Beautiful!

1654
01:57:21,543 --> 01:57:22,771
They're alive!

1655
01:57:30,823 --> 01:57:32,381
Another wormhole!

1656
01:57:32,743 --> 01:57:34,495
This one's much more violent!

1657
01:59:04,223 --> 01:59:05,178
Some...

1658
01:59:06,503 --> 01:59:08,141
...celestial event...

1659
01:59:09,543 --> 01:59:10,498
No!

1660
01:59:11,383 --> 01:59:12,862
No words!

1661
01:59:13,303 --> 01:59:14,861
No words...

1662
01:59:16,503 --> 01:59:18,095
...to describe it!

1663
01:59:20,103 --> 01:59:21,502
Poetry!

1664
01:59:22,983 --> 01:59:24,462
They should have sent...

1665
01:59:25,143 --> 01:59:26,212
...a poet.

1666
01:59:26,743 --> 01:59:28,142
lt's so beautiful!

1667
01:59:29,343 --> 01:59:30,571
Beautiful!

1668
01:59:32,303 --> 01:59:34,055
So beautiful.

1669
01:59:38,423 --> 01:59:40,778
l had no idea.

1670
02:02:13,783 --> 02:02:15,011
Hi, Sparks.

1671
02:02:16,823 --> 02:02:17,778
Dad?

1672
02:02:25,463 --> 02:02:26,942
l missed you.

1673
02:02:32,703 --> 02:02:33,658
Aren't you...?

1674
02:02:33,863 --> 02:02:36,616
l'm sorry l couldn't
be there for you, sweetheart.

1675
02:02:46,423 --> 02:02:47,697
You're not real.

1676
02:02:49,623 --> 02:02:50,976
None of this is real!

1677
02:02:51,223 --> 02:02:52,861
That's my scientist.

1678
02:02:54,183 --> 02:02:58,301
When l was unconscious, you
downloaded my thoughts, my memories.

1679
02:02:59,263 --> 02:03:00,537
Pensacola!

1680
02:03:03,703 --> 02:03:06,058
We thought it might
make things easier for you.

1681
02:03:19,303 --> 02:03:20,702
Why did you contact us?

1682
02:03:20,863 --> 02:03:22,455
You contacted us.

1683
02:03:22,983 --> 02:03:24,541
We were just listening.

1684
02:03:25,343 --> 02:03:26,617
There are others?

1685
02:03:26,943 --> 02:03:28,058
Many others.

1686
02:03:32,983 --> 02:03:34,132
They all...

1687
02:03:34,623 --> 02:03:37,660
...travel here through
that transit system you built?

1688
02:03:38,103 --> 02:03:39,582
We didn't build it.

1689
02:03:40,663 --> 02:03:42,142
We don't know who did.

1690
02:03:44,103 --> 02:03:46,617
They were gone
long before we ever got here.

1691
02:03:47,543 --> 02:03:49,295
Maybe someday they'll come back.

1692
02:03:50,263 --> 02:03:52,731
All the civilizations
you find come here?

1693
02:03:52,903 --> 02:03:54,097
Not all.

1694
02:03:55,783 --> 02:03:58,775
-ls this some test?
-No, no test.

1695
02:04:01,663 --> 02:04:03,096
You have your mother's hands.

1696
02:04:12,903 --> 02:04:14,973
You're an interesting species...

1697
02:04:15,583 --> 02:04:17,175
...an interesting mix.

1698
02:04:18,423 --> 02:04:21,017
You're capable
of such beautiful dreams...

1699
02:04:22,023 --> 02:04:24,059
...and such horrible nightmares.

1700
02:04:25,543 --> 02:04:27,295
You feel so lost...

1701
02:04:28,023 --> 02:04:30,457
...so cut off, so alone.

1702
02:04:32,103 --> 02:04:33,331
Only you're not.

1703
02:04:37,663 --> 02:04:39,255
ln all our searching...

1704
02:04:39,423 --> 02:04:42,256
...all we've found
that makes the emptiness bearable...

1705
02:04:42,943 --> 02:04:44,342
...is each other.

1706
02:04:48,103 --> 02:04:49,661
What happens now?

1707
02:04:50,943 --> 02:04:52,012
Now?

1708
02:04:53,343 --> 02:04:54,742
You go home.

1709
02:04:55,263 --> 02:04:56,252
Home?

1710
02:04:56,703 --> 02:04:57,772
But...

1711
02:04:58,303 --> 02:04:59,656
...l have so many questions.

1712
02:05:00,063 --> 02:05:01,621
Do we get to come back?

1713
02:05:02,663 --> 02:05:04,415
This was just a first step.

1714
02:05:05,023 --> 02:05:06,741
ln time, you'll take another.

1715
02:05:08,223 --> 02:05:10,657
But other people need to see
what l've seen...

1716
02:05:10,823 --> 02:05:13,735
This is the way it's been done
for billions of years.

1717
02:05:16,023 --> 02:05:17,615
Small moves, Ellie.

1718
02:05:19,423 --> 02:05:21,015
Small moves.

1719
02:06:02,743 --> 02:06:04,335
We've got video on Ellie!

1720
02:06:04,543 --> 02:06:06,420
She's through!
She is in the net.

1721
02:06:06,583 --> 02:06:08,858
She's alive.
Get the President on the phone!

1722
02:06:09,663 --> 02:06:11,142
What's going on?
How is she?

1723
02:06:11,943 --> 02:06:13,581
Ellie, this is Control.
You copy?

1724
02:06:13,823 --> 02:06:15,176
-What's going on?
-l don't know.

1725
02:06:15,903 --> 02:06:17,416
-She's alive.
-Put her on P.A.

1726
02:06:17,663 --> 02:06:19,096
Ellie, hold on tight.

1727
02:06:19,743 --> 02:06:22,894
We're still trying to determine
the nature of the malfunction...

1728
02:06:23,103 --> 02:06:25,537
...but the important thing
is you're okay.

1729
02:06:25,783 --> 02:06:26,738
<i>What?</i>

1730
02:06:27,063 --> 02:06:28,462
lt's all right.

1731
02:06:28,663 --> 02:06:30,460
The important thing is you're safe.

1732
02:06:31,423 --> 02:06:33,175
<i>What malfunction?</i>

1733
02:06:37,383 --> 02:06:38,657
<i>What happened?</i>

1734
02:06:40,223 --> 02:06:41,702
<i>What day is this?</i>

1735
02:06:42,463 --> 02:06:43,418
l'm sorry.

1736
02:06:43,623 --> 02:06:45,022
Did you say what day?

1737
02:06:46,623 --> 02:06:48,056
<i>How long was I gone?</i>

1738
02:06:50,303 --> 02:06:54,296
The lPV dropped
straight through the Machine.

1739
02:06:55,143 --> 02:06:56,815
You didn't go anywhere.

1740
02:06:57,503 --> 02:06:58,777
But l did.

1741
02:06:59,103 --> 02:07:00,331
l did go.

1742
02:07:00,863 --> 02:07:02,933
That's what l've tried
to tell everyone.

1743
02:07:07,383 --> 02:07:09,817
But the headset
didn't record a single image?

1744
02:07:10,503 --> 02:07:11,731
Just this.

1745
02:07:12,023 --> 02:07:13,012
Static.

1746
02:07:13,183 --> 02:07:14,138
Thank you.

1747
02:07:15,583 --> 02:07:17,221
Let me show you what we saw.

1748
02:07:26,823 --> 02:07:30,293
43 separate remote cameras
show exactly the same event.

1749
02:07:30,623 --> 02:07:33,933
The lPV dropped straight through.
Everyone saw exactly...

1750
02:07:34,263 --> 02:07:35,582
...the same thing.

1751
02:07:35,903 --> 02:07:37,336
Nothing happened.

1752
02:07:38,903 --> 02:07:40,814
How do you explain this, Doctor?

1753
02:07:42,943 --> 02:07:44,092
l can't.

1754
02:07:44,263 --> 02:07:45,662
<i>I'd encourage you...</i>

1755
02:07:47,383 --> 02:07:49,499
<i>...not to inflame this situation...</i>

1756
02:07:49,663 --> 02:07:51,415
<i>...beyond the facts.</i>

1757
02:07:51,583 --> 02:07:54,655
<i>Let us deal with this on the facts.</i>

1758
02:07:54,943 --> 02:07:57,821
<i>We are monitoring</i>
<i>what has actually happened.</i>

1759
02:07:57,983 --> 02:08:00,941
<i>We are taking</i>
<i>what we believe are factually...</i>

1760
02:08:01,143 --> 02:08:03,054
<i>...appropriate steps.</i>

1761
02:08:03,343 --> 02:08:06,301
<i>Amid a flurry of accusations</i>
<i>and counter</i>-<i>accusations...</i>

1762
02:08:06,463 --> 02:08:09,023
<i>...by the nations representing</i>
<i>the Machine Consortium...</i>

1763
02:08:09,223 --> 02:08:11,942
<i>...the President has ordered</i>
<i>a special inquiry.</i>

1764
02:08:12,103 --> 02:08:14,822
<i>But the appointment</i>
<i>to the committee of Michael Kitz...</i>

1765
02:08:14,983 --> 02:08:17,702
<i>... who has resigned</i>
<i>as National Security Advisor...</i>

1766
02:08:17,903 --> 02:08:20,212
<i>...has raised eyebrows</i>
<i>on Capitol Hill.</i>

1767
02:08:20,423 --> 02:08:23,938
<i>I have made no decision to run for</i>
<i>Congress, announced no candidacy.</i>

1768
02:08:24,183 --> 02:08:27,380
<i>I resigned as</i>
<i>National Security Advisor...</i>

1769
02:08:27,583 --> 02:08:31,542
<i>...in order to devote</i>
<i>all of my energy to this inquiry.</i>

1770
02:08:32,263 --> 02:08:36,700
<i>The people of the world have a right</i>
<i>to know what really happened.</i>

1771
02:08:37,503 --> 02:08:40,063
Yet every scientific
instrument confirms...

1772
02:08:40,223 --> 02:08:44,057
...the lPV was out of contact
for only a fraction of a second.

1773
02:08:44,223 --> 02:08:45,975
lsn't that correct, Doctor?

1774
02:08:47,863 --> 02:08:50,093
A fraction of a second Earth time,
yes.

1775
02:08:50,903 --> 02:08:52,222
Earth time?

1776
02:08:52,423 --> 02:08:55,733
Senator, l believe that the Machine
opened up a wormhole...

1777
02:08:56,103 --> 02:09:00,540
...a tunnel through space-time, also
known as an Einstein-Rossen Bridge.

1778
02:09:00,863 --> 02:09:04,856
Due to the effect of general relativity,
what l experienced as 18 hours...

1779
02:09:05,023 --> 02:09:07,218
...passed instantaneously on Earth.

1780
02:09:07,423 --> 02:09:11,382
lsn't it true these wormholes
are merely theoretical predictions?

1781
02:09:11,743 --> 02:09:14,257
There is no evidence
they actually exist?

1782
02:09:14,463 --> 02:09:16,055
There is no direct evidence, no.

1783
02:09:16,383 --> 02:09:17,498
Tell me...

1784
02:09:17,943 --> 02:09:20,776
...why would these aliens
go to all this trouble?

1785
02:09:21,343 --> 02:09:25,222
Bring you thousands of light years,
then send you home without proof?

1786
02:09:25,863 --> 02:09:28,502
They said it's how it's been done
for billions of years.

1787
02:09:29,023 --> 02:09:32,174
<i>You have no proof because</i>
<i>they didn't want you to have any.</i>

1788
02:09:32,543 --> 02:09:34,420
<i>A phenomenon known</i>
<i>in psychiatric circles...</i>

1789
02:09:34,583 --> 02:09:36,858
<i>...as a self</i>-<i>reinforcing delusion.</i>

1790
02:09:37,663 --> 02:09:39,062
<i>You think I was delusional?</i>

1791
02:09:39,303 --> 02:09:43,262
<i>I do think you may have suffered</i>
<i>some kind of an episode. Yes, I do.</i>

1792
02:09:43,423 --> 02:09:46,142
<i>I'd like to propose</i>
<i>an alternate hypothesis...</i>

1793
02:09:46,303 --> 02:09:49,852
<i>...and I'd like you to bring your</i>
<i>scientific expertise to bear on it.</i>

1794
02:09:50,143 --> 02:09:53,021
To fake a signal from Vega...

1795
02:09:53,783 --> 02:09:55,011
...what would you need?

1796
02:09:56,863 --> 02:10:00,492
You'd need a satellite to transmit
it, but it would be impossible to...

1797
02:10:00,703 --> 02:10:04,491
You'd need a satellite
and launch capabilities to orbit it.

1798
02:10:04,663 --> 02:10:07,780
And the message itself. To put
something like this together...

1799
02:10:08,023 --> 02:10:10,218
...so complex,
drawing on many disciplines...

1800
02:10:10,383 --> 02:10:11,657
Would be impossible.

1801
02:10:13,423 --> 02:10:14,902
lmpossible?

1802
02:10:15,343 --> 02:10:18,141
ls there anyone who might
have been up to the challenge?

1803
02:10:19,023 --> 02:10:21,457
Someone with extraordinary
technical expertise...

1804
02:10:21,703 --> 02:10:23,614
...enormous financial resources...

1805
02:10:24,063 --> 02:10:27,976
...someone perverse enough, eccentric
enough to come up with the idea?

1806
02:10:29,623 --> 02:10:30,339
Hadden?

1807
02:10:31,423 --> 02:10:33,334
S. R. Hadden.

1808
02:10:37,663 --> 02:10:39,255
You're implying that this was...

1809
02:10:39,463 --> 02:10:41,931
...some kind of a hoax?
That he engineered this?

1810
02:10:42,103 --> 02:10:43,377
S. R. Hadden...

1811
02:10:43,743 --> 02:10:48,055
<i>...a legendary power broker in</i>
<i>perhaps his final bid for immortality.</i>

1812
02:10:48,383 --> 02:10:50,943
<i>Maybe he wanted to</i>
<i>exploit new technologies...</i>

1813
02:10:51,103 --> 02:10:53,219
<i>...having world governments</i>
<i>pick up the tab.</i>

1814
02:10:53,383 --> 02:10:56,056
<i>Perhaps this was his</i>
<i>final altruistic gesture...</i>

1815
02:10:56,263 --> 02:10:59,733
<i>...to unite the world in some</i>
<i>common goal. Maybe all of the above.</i>

1816
02:11:00,103 --> 02:11:02,139
<i>S. R. Hadden, a brilliant...</i>

1817
02:11:02,783 --> 02:11:04,375
<i>...and complicated man.</i>

1818
02:11:07,103 --> 02:11:10,778
Doctor, are you familiar
with the scientific precept...

1819
02:11:11,423 --> 02:11:13,414
...known as Occam's Razor?

1820
02:11:19,423 --> 02:11:20,492
Yes.

1821
02:11:22,423 --> 02:11:26,939
lt means the simplest explanation
generally tends to be the right one.

1822
02:11:27,103 --> 02:11:28,058
Exactly.

1823
02:11:28,783 --> 02:11:31,172
You tell me.
What is more likely here?

1824
02:11:31,383 --> 02:11:34,614
A message from aliens
results in a magical machine...

1825
02:11:34,783 --> 02:11:37,377
...that whisks you
to the center of the galaxy...

1826
02:11:37,583 --> 02:11:40,302
...to windsurf with Dad
and a split second later...

1827
02:11:40,503 --> 02:11:43,859
...returns you home
without a single shred of proof?

1828
02:11:44,263 --> 02:11:47,573
Or that your experience
is the result of being...

1829
02:11:47,743 --> 02:11:51,053
...the unwitting star in the
farewell performance of one...

1830
02:11:51,223 --> 02:11:52,133
...S.R. Hadden?

1831
02:11:52,343 --> 02:11:55,892
A man with the means and motive
to play you and all of us...

1832
02:11:56,063 --> 02:12:00,215
...as pawns in the most elaborate,
most expensive hoax of all time?

1833
02:12:05,023 --> 02:12:08,538
You come to us with no evidence,
no records...

1834
02:12:09,263 --> 02:12:10,935
...no artifacts...

1835
02:12:11,263 --> 02:12:15,256
...only a story that, to put it
mildly, strains credibility.

1836
02:12:16,503 --> 02:12:19,381
Over half a trillion dollars
were spent.

1837
02:12:19,703 --> 02:12:22,058
Dozens of lives were lost.

1838
02:12:23,103 --> 02:12:27,301
Are you going to sit there and tell
us we should just take this all...

1839
02:12:28,343 --> 02:12:29,696
...on faith?

1840
02:12:33,583 --> 02:12:35,494
Please answer the question, Doctor.

1841
02:12:39,223 --> 02:12:41,293
ls it possible
that it didn't happen?

1842
02:12:41,543 --> 02:12:42,612
Yes.

1843
02:12:45,343 --> 02:12:48,380
As a scientist l must concede that.
l must volunteer that.

1844
02:12:52,663 --> 02:12:53,982
Let me get this straight.

1845
02:12:54,303 --> 02:12:58,137
You admit you have no physical
evidence to back up your story?

1846
02:12:58,703 --> 02:12:59,499
Yes.

1847
02:12:59,743 --> 02:13:02,655
You admit you may have
hallucinated this whole thing?

1848
02:13:03,543 --> 02:13:05,773
You admit if you were
in our position...

1849
02:13:05,943 --> 02:13:09,333
...you would be as incredulous
and skeptical as we?

1850
02:13:10,783 --> 02:13:14,617
Then why don't you simply withdraw
your testimony and concede...

1851
02:13:14,903 --> 02:13:18,816
...that this journey to the center
of the galaxy never took place?

1852
02:13:21,663 --> 02:13:23,415
Because l can't.

1853
02:13:30,103 --> 02:13:32,697
l had an experience.

1854
02:13:34,943 --> 02:13:37,503
l can't prove it.
l can't even explain it.

1855
02:13:37,663 --> 02:13:40,541
But everything l know as
a human being, everything l am...

1856
02:13:40,703 --> 02:13:42,773
...tells me it was real.

1857
02:13:45,143 --> 02:13:48,453
l was given something wonderful,
something that changed me forever.

1858
02:13:48,783 --> 02:13:49,818
A vision...

1859
02:13:50,343 --> 02:13:51,901
...of the universe...

1860
02:13:52,623 --> 02:13:54,693
...that tells us undeniably...

1861
02:13:55,143 --> 02:13:57,418
...how tiny and insignificant...

1862
02:13:57,583 --> 02:14:00,973
...and how rare and precious
we all are.

1863
02:14:02,103 --> 02:14:05,095
A vision that tells us
that we belong to something...

1864
02:14:05,343 --> 02:14:09,780
...that is greater than ourselves,
that none of us are alone.

1865
02:14:14,503 --> 02:14:17,381
l wish l could share that.

1866
02:14:20,783 --> 02:14:21,852
l wish...

1867
02:14:23,423 --> 02:14:25,778
...that everyone, if even for one...

1868
02:14:26,103 --> 02:14:27,252
...moment...

1869
02:14:27,503 --> 02:14:28,731
...could feel...

1870
02:14:29,183 --> 02:14:32,061
...that awe and humility and hope.

1871
02:14:41,063 --> 02:14:43,213
That continues to be my wish.

1872
02:15:22,743 --> 02:15:25,257
Dr. Arroway,
can l get a picture, please.

1873
02:16:05,583 --> 02:16:06,652
Reverend Joss!

1874
02:16:06,863 --> 02:16:08,421
What do you believe?!

1875
02:16:14,063 --> 02:16:17,897
As a person of faith, l'm bound by a
different covenant than Dr. Arroway.

1876
02:16:19,663 --> 02:16:21,733
But our goal is one and the same.

1877
02:16:22,223 --> 02:16:23,815
The pursuit of truth.

1878
02:16:27,223 --> 02:16:28,451
l, for one, believe her.

1879
02:16:51,023 --> 02:16:53,856
<i>So what happens now?</i>
<i>We give her a medal?</i>

1880
02:16:54,263 --> 02:16:56,572
l'd say at least a healthy grant.

1881
02:16:56,943 --> 02:17:00,219
You read the confidential report
from the investigating committee?

1882
02:17:00,423 --> 02:17:01,776
<i>I flipped through it.</i>

1883
02:17:02,223 --> 02:17:06,341
l was very interested in the section
on Arroway's video unit.

1884
02:17:07,023 --> 02:17:09,253
The one that recorded the static.

1885
02:17:10,543 --> 02:17:11,771
<i>Continue.</i>

1886
02:17:12,743 --> 02:17:15,974
The fact that it recorded static
isn't what interests me.

1887
02:17:21,103 --> 02:17:22,331
<i>Continue.</i>

1888
02:17:23,183 --> 02:17:24,980
What interests me...

1889
02:17:25,263 --> 02:17:28,812
...is that it recorded
approximately 18 hours of it.

1890
02:17:33,863 --> 02:17:35,660
<i>That is interesting, isn't it?</i>

1891
02:17:42,103 --> 02:17:45,891
And you can see over there,
we're building 45 brand new dishes.

1892
02:17:46,143 --> 02:17:49,818
That means when you put them together
with all the radio telescopes...

1893
02:17:50,023 --> 02:17:51,342
...all over the world...

1894
02:17:51,543 --> 02:17:55,741
...we'll hear farther into space
than anyone has ever heard before.

1895
02:17:57,223 --> 02:18:00,021
Are there other people
out there in the universe?

1896
02:18:00,943 --> 02:18:02,296
That's a good question.

1897
02:18:02,543 --> 02:18:03,612
What do you think?

1898
02:18:04,223 --> 02:18:05,178
l don't know.

1899
02:18:05,623 --> 02:18:07,102
That's a good answer.

1900
02:18:08,303 --> 02:18:09,258
Skeptic, huh?

1901
02:18:10,503 --> 02:18:14,860
The important thing is that you all
keep searching for your own answers.

1902
02:18:15,343 --> 02:18:17,299
One thing about the universe,
though.

1903
02:18:18,223 --> 02:18:19,338
The universe...

1904
02:18:19,823 --> 02:18:21,893
...is a pretty big place.

1905
02:18:22,863 --> 02:18:25,093
lt's bigger than anything...

1906
02:18:25,463 --> 02:18:28,182
...anyone has ever
dreamed of before.

1907
02:18:29,703 --> 02:18:31,341
So if it's just us...

1908
02:18:33,103 --> 02:18:35,173
...it seems like
an awful waste of space.

1909
02:18:36,983 --> 02:18:37,938
Right?

1910
02:27:41,623 --> 02:27:43,614
